  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe logic between the message handler and syncing should be separated and split into separate threads. The message handler currently handles all decoding and validation of messages before passing them onto the sync manager. We should add responding to RPC messages to the list of message handler duties. The message handler now also determines whether objects should be forwarded across the network.\r\n\r\nAs the message handler and sync manager are currently run in a single thread, the block propagation speed of Lighthouse and it's ability to receive and respond to network messages can be delayed during syncing or heavy block processing.\r\n\r\nMore specifically the two should perform the following tasks:\r\n\r\nMessage Handler \r\n- Validate input messages\r\n- Decode input messages\r\n- Respond to RPC requests\r\n\r\nSync Manager\r\n- Process Objects (blocks/attestations..) from the gossipsub layer\r\n- Manage syncing - Request and manage required blocks from the RPC and process them.\r\n- Manage connected peers and their block availabilities\r\n\r\nIn this update, we should probably prevent lighthouse from responding to RPC requests whilst in full sync mode. ",
